  "publisher": "image_comics",
  "about": "Conquest is a supervillain appearing in the American comic book series Invincible and Invincible Universe: Battle Beast, created by writer Robert Kirkman and artist Ryan Ottley. He first appeared in Invincible #61, published by Image Comics in August 2009. Conquest is a high-ranking member of the Viltrum Empire, and one of the most brutal villains in the series.\nConquest is one of the strongest and most experienced members of the alien race known as the Viltrumites. He survived both the Great Purge, a planet-wide civil conflict, and the Scourge Virus, a bioengineered disease that decimated the Viltrumite population and inflicted lasting damage on most of the survivors. \nDue to his weakened condition, Conquest was gravely injured in combat with several Rognarrs, members of a savage alien species so powerful they could rival his strength. The assault left him with a missing right arm, a scarred face, and the loss of his right eye. In spite of these lasting disabilities, Conquest equipped himself with a prosthetic arm and remained in service to the Viltrumite Empire.\nConquest was brought into play after the \"Invincible War\" comic book tale as a way to raise the stakes of the current struggle involving Mark Grayson (Invincible) and the Viltrumite Empire.",
  "note": null,
  "source": "image_comics"
